SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE FOR
HOUSE COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 3004
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
3975S.03C KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To amend chapter 407, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to the sale of wood
products.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Chapter 407, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto
2 one new section, to be known as section 407.3300, to read as
3 follows:
1 407.3300. 1. No person, company, or business shall
2 sell or market products in a manner that is false or
3 misleading by using the term "wood" to describe the material
4 composition of a product or component without the product's
5 decorative surface being made of solid wood or wood veneer,
6 originating from a tree. No person, company, or business
7 shall advertise or sell in a manner that is false or
8 misleading any part of a product marketed as wood using wood-
9 related terms or names of wood species including, but not
10 limited to, oak, maple, cherry, pine, and walnut if the
11 product's decorative surface is not that wood species.
12 2. A person, company, or business may sell any product
13 physically located within the state as of August 28, 2026,
14 that is packaged in violation of the provisions of
15 subsection 1 of this section if the product is clearly
16 labeled: "This product is not made from wood.". After

SCS HCS HB 3004 2
17 August 28, 2026, no additional products shall enter the
18 state if the packaging is in violation of subsection 1 of
19 this section.
20 3. The department of agriculture may promulgate all
21 necessary rules and regulations for the administration of
22 this section. Any rule or portion of a rule, as that term
23 is defined in section 536.010, that is created under the
24 authority delegated in this section shall become effective
25 only if it complies with and is subject to all of the
26 provisions of chapter 536 and, if applicable, section
27 536.028. This section and chapter 536 are nonseverable and
28 if any of the powers vested with the general assembly
29 pursuant to chapter 536 to review, to delay the effective
30 date, or to disapprove and annul a rule are subsequently
31 held unconstitutional, then the grant of rulemaking
32 authority and any rule proposed or adopted after August 28,
33 2026, shall be invalid and void.
